Where do you feel most at ease? What elements bring you there? How can you prioritize more time in that place? These are some questions I like to ask my nutrition clients — a lot of mental and physical tension arises from intrinsically being in the wrong environment. The ocean has soothed me since the beginning of time, and I know I can always return to it for a reset. This season has many of us reflecting and taking inventory on our lives — I encourage you to make space & simmer on these answers as you enter the new year. 💭

Equal parts beautiful & nourishing 🍊 winter citrus is an antioxidant-rich haven, protecting us from damaging free radicals and oxidative stress. Vitamin C is the star of the show here and essential for strengthened immunity during the colder months — my favorite seasonal sources are grapefruit, lemon, broccoli, cauliflower, brussels sprouts, tomatoes, and kale. A little bit goes a long way here, so no need to incorporate them all at once! Just a few servings are you’re golden. #holisticnutrition

Cultivating a career that blends purpose and passion has been no easy feat. I have consciously kept a lot behind the scenes in fear of failure, but it’s time to draw back the curtains and share what I’ve been up to! When I launched my nutrition business in 2021, I wasn’t sure what the trajectory looked like. One of my greatest takeaways as an entrepreneur is that you will be rewarded for taking thoughtful risks. Self doubt, imposter syndrome, it’s all part of pursuing what lights you up. As soon as I started taking on clients and seeing their health transformations, I promised myself that I would put my whole heart into it as soon as I could. It’s cliché, but helping others has always been at the root of my being. It was a slow build…I was taking calls before and after my full time job, on the weekends, & on the road. I have been so fortunate to work with people of varied backgrounds from all over the world, from college students to CEO's, new mom's to couples, athletes to artists. I quickly identified the common denominator: a desire for BALANCE. In an extremist society, the majority of the population is looking for a quick fix with an all or nothing mentality. We overlook the innate desire to ENJOY life whilst also feeling good inside and out. There’s a misconception that we cannot have both simultaneously and I’m here to debunk that notion. My practice is founded in building a sustainable lifestyle that grants you the joy of food, community, and flexibility. It has been such a gift to connect with many of you on a personal level through my sessions. This is only the beginning! I could’ve never done this without this platform to build from – so this is me saying THANK YOU! Never hesitate to send me a message if you'd like to learn more or have any questions about my sessions, creative work, etc. 🤍

Balance looks different for everyone! My nutrition practice is founded in bio-individuality, which means that what works for one, may not work for all. When thinking about daily routines, I prioritize what makes me *feel* good first - comparison is the thief of joy in various aspects of our lives, so I encourage my clients to look inward when developing healthy habits. For me — nourishment, daily movement, creative outlets, personal connections, time spent outside, and a calm & clean space are some consistent pillars that make me feel grounded. What are yours?

It can be really challenging to stay healthy during the change of seasons - I love implementing a rotation of products from @iHerb to support and strengthen my immunity, especially during transitional temperatures. From the morning to the evening, there’s many small ways to make a big impact on your overall wellness. 🧘🏻‍♀️ Whether it’s diffusing lavender as a calming ritual, incorporating B12 and probiotics, adding anti-inflammatory powders like turmeric to a nutrient rich smoothie, carving out time for exercise, going outside, taking care of your skin, or cooking a delicious meal - they’re all pieces of the health puzzle. @iHerb is an incredible and accessible one stop shop. Check out the products I featured here and save 20% using my code ASHLEYM on their website. #ad #iHerb
